  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Right now, a script runs with the extra parameter `--network` on the command line, I'm seeing that if we could have script specify its own network configuration, it would be better. So I don't need to remember which script matches with which network.\r\n\r\nI suggest we add another function name within script:\r\n\r\n```\r\ndef setup_network():\r\n    return {\"cmd_setttings\": \"xxx\"}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt returns a network configuration that can be used for connection.\r\n\r\nIf this is useful to other people, or it's the right approach, I'm happy to contribute.",
